715038f-a.text:
East 111th Street, north side, from Second to First Avenue's, as photographed from the Second Avenue "E1" line. At the right is the Jefferson Park Boys Club. This is at No. 329, a site occupied in 1922 by the two story structure of the Liberman Dairy Co. The vacant
lot shown is on the First Avenue side.
1: June 7, 1940
2: About 1936
P. L. Sperr
